-- CarMax Shares Surge After First-Quarter Profit Tops Analysts' Estimates
-- Theo Keith
-- 2010-06-23T14:30:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/carmax-shares-surge-after-first-quarter-profit-tops-analysts-estimates.html

          
          
             CarMax Inc., the largest U.S. seller
of used cars, rose the most in nine months after first-quarter
profit topped analysts’  estimates .  
 CarMax climbed $1.45, or 7.3 percent, to $21.45 at 10:29
a.m. in New York Stock Exchange composite  trading . The shares
earlier increased as much as 10 percent, the  biggest intraday
gain  since Sept. 22.  
 Profit in the period ended May 31 more than tripled from a
year earlier to $101.1 million, or 44 cents a share, Richmond,
Virginia-based CarMax said today in a statement. The average
 estimate  of 15 analysts surveyed by Bloomberg was 33 cents.  
 Same-store sales gained 9 percent amid a “gradual” rebound
in customer traffic, Chief Executive Officer  Thomas Folliard 
said in the statement. CarMax was chosen to replace XTO Energy
Inc. in the  Standard & Poor’s 500 Index , S&P said yesterday on
its website.  
